cutting long sleeved tops if i cut a long sleeved top to make it short sleeved how do i protect the ends so they don't get ruined frayed i can't sew to save my life and have no other ideas go to walmart or some other store that has a fabric section ask the person working there for hemming tape its a double sided tape for fabric obviously if you want to go from a long sleeve to a sleeve on the upper part of your arm you can go ahead and cut the sleeve to the elbow try the shirt on and figure out where you want the sleeves to end fold the sleeves back to that point and carefully take the shirt off turn it inside out now you have the sleeves at the point you want them put the tape at the edge of the sleeve and continue until the entire edge is lined with tape pull the extra part of the sleeve out so the entire sleeve is inside out fold it up again using the tape as a guide cut the excess off you may have to iron it to set if depending on the instructions repeat for other sleeve hope this helps Zipper Poker jargon Floppy disk Nine Inch Nails The Price Is Right Little Britain Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Futurama (TV series - season 3) Swingout Breaststroke EastEnders Good Times Eric Cartman Betting (poker) Aerial (dance move) Kodocha The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Knife Shoe Professional wrestling holds Professional wrestling throws The Inside Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sin City Computer and video game genres Revolver Good Morning, Vietnam Backstroke Singlish Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers Strap-on dildo Tokusatsu Object-oriented programming Atomic Kitten The Shining (film) Bob and George Rail tracks Indianapolis 500 Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Gesture Major League Baseball television contracts Butterfly stroke Textile manufacturing The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular The Angry Beavers Aladdin (1992 film) Rose (Doctor Who) Glossary of climbing terms Military history of the United Kingdom during World War II Liam Gallagher Beverly